n issue is the baby's vomiting and distended stomach.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050671,0.080499,0.084713,0.087594,0.09139,0.091763,0.092576,0.091239,0.088633,0.086187,0.080328,0.074408],"unified_progress":[0.045891,0.073594,0.083987,0.091794,0.095811,0.09751,0.096415,0.095417,0.092008,0.086616,0.07635,0.064608]},{"section":7,"text":"The baby is vomiting bile.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045853,0.07733,0.082512,0.082399,0.090305,0.09189,0.091535,0.091928,0.089604,0.090425,0.085765,0.080454],"unified_progress":[0.050772,0.08046,0.087564,0.09412,0.095192,0.097242,0.09521,0.093185,0.088695,0.08561,0.072807,0.059144]},{"section":8,"text":"Bile in vomit usually means that the stomach is full and the contents are moving backward into the esophagus.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038052,0.066544,0.083174,0.092757,0.099914,0.10107,0.10323,0.09893,0.094468,0.084214,0.074599,0.063048],"unified_progress":[0.038282,0.070776,0.091419,0.10405,0.10658,0.10695,0.10169,0.095109,0.094571,0.078084,0.062704,0.049773]},{"section":9,"text":"Since the baby is so young, this could be due to a blockage or obstruction somewhere in the gastrointestinal tract.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044247,0.07284,0.084253,0.093668,0.096129,0.097568,0.10002,0.09745,0.093688,0.084823,0.074101,0.061212],"unified_progress":[0.042444,0.072087,0.087417,0.097478,0.102,0.10374,0.10099,0.096639,0.093097,0.082399,0.068287,0.053422]},{"section":10,"text":"The fact that only small amounts of meconium have passed suggests that the intestines might be blocked, preventing the normal passage of meconium, which is the baby's first stool.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040518,0.063773,0.079234,0.089219,0.096987,0.099775,0.10261,0.10057,0.09716,0.088094,0.077426,0.064637],"unified_progress":[0.037434,0.066321,0.085549,0.095679,0.10191,0.10764,0.10279,0.098176,0.094874,0.084066,0.070197,0.055359]},{"section":11,"text":"So, possible causes of obstruction could be something like a congenital malformation.","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030774,0.054537,0.071216,0.083346,0.091987,0.099129,0.10426,0.10609,0.10437,0.099963,0.085317,0.069011],"unified_progress":[0.033694,0.066787,0.084499,0.097215,0.099314,0.10003,0.10189,0.09902,0.094204,0.090133,0.075219,0.057992]},{"section":12,"text":"One common obstruction in newborns is pyloric stenosis, which is a narrowing of the opening from the stomach to the small intestine.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035212,0.060882,0.07828,0.090515,0.098488,0.10106,0.10638,0.10295,0.097287,0.087205,0.076436,0.06531],"unified_progress":[0.036591,0.0689,0.088904,0.10196,0.10689,0.10647,0.10253,0.097099,0.093705,0.079395,0.065487,0.052068]},{"section":13,"text":"This would cause the stomach to distend because the stomach can't empty properly into the intestines.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040543,0.063118,0.081107,0.094304,0.10147,0.10301,0.10588,0.1001,0.094508,0.082262,0.072243,0.061454],"unified_progress":[0.037287,0.069354,0.089879,0.10297,0.1095,0.10763,0.10347,0.095969,0.09509,0.077156,0.06206,0.049644]},{"section":14,"text":"The baby would vomit forcefully, sometimes projectile, and since the stomach is full, the vomit can include bile.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035339,0.058496,0.075408,0.085152,0.096148,0.10082,0.10491,0.10436,0.10181,0.091449,0.080699,0.065397],"unified_progress":[0.038148,0.066468,0.084732,0.096475,0.10144,0.11914,0.10531,0.099237,0.092723,0.082681,0.065086,0.048557]},{"section":15,"text":"Another possibility is duodenal atresia, which is a blockage in the duodenum, the first part of the small intestine.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033032,0.059739,0.078325,0.09