o consider if there's any other condition that could cause bile vomiting and distension.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031309,0.050039,0.067108,0.076037,0.087938,0.094922,0.098167,0.10253,0.10303,0.10953,0.095877,0.083504],"unified_progress":[0.032085,0.061364,0.07651,0.090052,0.092945,0.095686,0.09989,0.099334,0.09794,0.10017,0.08617,0.067857]},{"section":21,"text":"Maybe something like a hernia or a motility disorder, but pyloric stenosis is more straightforward and fits the presentation better.","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031936,0.050309,0.065709,0.076862,0.086549,0.093808,0.10185,0.10554,0.10689,0.10321,0.094832,0.082506],"unified_progress":[0.032672,0.057579,0.073692,0.084463,0.091599,0.09709,0.099147,0.10091,0.10019,0.098133,0.088761,0.075766]},{"section":22,"text":"So, putting it all together, the baby's symptoms\u2014vomiting bile, distended stomach, minimal meconium passage\u2014point towards pyloric stenosis as the most likely diagnosis.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025108,0.042909,0.049983,0.054693,0.061917,0.067412,0.073876,0.082348,0.089987,0.11428,0.14378,0.19371],"unified_progress":[0.025776,0.042295,0.048306,0.056714,0.061079,0.073326,0.075978,0.087372,0.09693,0.10429,0.13957,0.18836]},{"section":23,"text":"The baby's symptoms, including bile-containing vomiting, distended stomach, and minimal meconium passage, suggest an obstruction in the gastrointestinal tract.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030211,0.05066,0.053212,0.054794,0.061924,0.067171,0.074496,0.083197,0.091583,0.10544,0.14508,0.18223],"unified_progress":[0.045487,0.064576,0.060377,0.061553,0.064496,0.07234,0.074019,0.08588,0.092325,0.098173,0.12203,0.15874]},{"section":24,"text":"Pyloric stenosis, a narrowing of the pylorus, fits well as it causes the stomach to distend and prevents proper emptying, leading to the described symptoms.","dimen